The male patient who contracted the virus via community transmission is in a hospital in Cork, where his diagnosis was made a number of days after admission, giving rise to the potential of contact with health workers, Dr Tony Holohan, Chief Medical Officer with the Department of Health told a news conference. Cork University Hospital (CUH) said on Twitter that strict visiting restrictions had been put in place at the hospital due to infection control concerns, with all outpatient appointments on Friday canceled. (Reporting by Padraic Halpin; Editing by Sandra Maler ) Please note you must be a Maverick Insider to comment. Sign up here or sign in if you are already an Insider.